cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.CY, cs.SE, cs.DC

This paper deals with the security requirements for remote authentication with password-protected smart cards and memory sticks. It focuses on the protection of password-based authentication between a client and a remote server, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of smart cards and memory sticks, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and cyber-physical systems (cs.CY). Additionally, the paper addresses the issue of credential storage, which is relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
